name: Starbucks

name: Mendon Ponds park

Down towards the pond Hopkins point
Sometimes restrooms are locked other times they are open. There are other restrooms in a park that I think are non gender-specific and it's a safe place. Down by the Birdsong nature trail common Wild Wings, and nature center, there is also restroom that is both genders and locks It is a safe restroom
comment: There are several single stalls. Not gender-specific. One is handicap accessible that says but the door sticks so be advised to maybe have a friend outside help me with it. The door opens outward and closes by itself so if not close hard it shouldn't stick but it wouldn't lock.

name: Hobgood Park
directions: Park in the main entrance with the "Holiday Lights of Hope" sign. Go into the fenced area with the baseball fields, and follow the signs that say "restrooms." The stalls are located past the concession stand.
comment: There are 10 single-stall gendered restrooms in the main area, with the unisex stall on the side of the far wall of the same building. There are also 2 additional gendered stalls near the tennis court.

name: Spirits Tavern

name: UNG Rec Center/Gym
directions: Go inside the gym, go up the stairs to the left of the entrance, take a sharp right and go down the short hallway to the right of the water fountains. The bathroom is the door in the right.
comment: You need a student ID card to enter the gym. If you’re a student and can get in, you’ll be safe using that bathroom. Just be sure to lock the door properly (:

name: Dunlap Hall, Georgia Cir, Dahlonega, GA 30533, USA
directions: It’s on the middle floor of the building on the left side of the long hall that connects Dunlap Hall to Newton Oakes Hall. It is to the right of the girls bathroom and to the left of a classroom door.
comment: No one will question you, it will either be a busy hallway or an empty hallway. The students are either 100% accepting or are too tired to care. I’ve used that bathroom many times, you’ll be safe <3
